  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220ºC/ 200ºC (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop half your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Grate the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677584010210-x200.jpeg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677584010210-x400.jpeg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677584010210-x700.jpeg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677584010210-x1000.jpeg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677584010210-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>meat-free</strong> <strong>mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!), <strong>grated onion</strong>,<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a bowl and give everything a good mix up (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Divide the<strong> meatball mixture</strong> and shape them into 4 meatballs per person</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677584013828-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677584013828-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677584013828-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677584013828-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677584013828-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> meatballs</strong> and cook for 4-5 min, turning occasionally, or until they’re browned all over</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677584017641-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677584017641-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677584017641-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677584017641-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677584017641-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meatballs are browned, transfer them to a plate and return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
